1.This certificate is being issued for RERA compliance for the firm (Tulsi Construction) for the project name The Capital and is based on the records and documents produced before me and explanations provided to me by the partner of the Firm; based on the verification of books of accounts till (date) 30.11.2024.
2.The details mentioned in such as carpet area, booking status, unit consideration, date of agreement to sale, encumbrance status, name, KYC and mobile numbers of allottees are as provided by the management.
Received amount has been verified with the books of accounts.
3. The agreement value for flat No.2 is Rs 26,00,000/- (i.e. inclusive of taxes and stamp duty) therefore in annexure to Form-3 the sale value is shown Rs23,24,000/- i.e. exclusive of taxes and stamp duty.
4. Actual Cost of Construction incurred and paid as per the books of accounts is Rs. 4,87,45,500/- which is more that the total estimated cost of Rs 3,80,00,000/-. 
5. Till date of this certificate as per the Books of Accounts and Bank Statement, the prompter has withdrawn total amount of Rs.7,77,48,500 /-. This calculation shows that this amount is higher than the limit as determined at Sr. No. 6 of the certificate. however, actual limit of withdrawal is higher that the limit at Sr No. 6. The reason for difference in  actual withdrawal limit  and withdrawal limit at sr, no. 6 is due to lower estimation of construction cost in comparison the actual cost incurred. The system  calculate the withdrawl limit by considering the estimated cost amount only.
